Try crossing many outdoors zones as a mage.<br>
You can have the pet up, or Invisibility, not both.<br>
If oyu have the pet up it's highly likely to attract aggro on its own, never mind you. Note also many Kunark zones mobs see invis.<br>
mages have *no* way to deal with mobs bar nuke/pet/run.<br>
Until lvl 54 when you get Scars of Sigil (450 hp bolt fire 2 sec cast). So generally for a hell of a long time mages have to run like hell to avoid ANY mob that isnt utterly utterly green.<br>
For example I aggroed a drolvarg rager in DL, what would a wiz do? it was light blue to me at 60, it got me to about        2/3 or 1/2 health at lvl 60 as I nuked it down with Scars.<br>
(just decided that enough was enough and that day I was NOT oging to run and the MOB was gonna get vaped:&gt;)<br>
I coudltn use my epic, 20 sec cast time, sure cant run over DL with epic up, recast it all tim each zone ugh no way.<br>
<br>
See what I mean? Wiz would snare/root nuke, epic absorb damage, few worries.<br>
<br>
Indoors, say Lguk, I can use pet as a battering ram and mob destroyer, few worries on mana (real nuisance on wizzies indoors is going OOM, wizzies need high lvl UBER efficient low damage nuke for dealing with greens etc lik 500 hp 100 mana at lvl 60), but I have to learn and deal with nutsoid pathing (Guk's pretty good that way, try the Hole, its sick)<br>
